<docs>
	<doc for="AsyncCallback">
		<summary>
			<para>References the callback method to be called when the asynchronous operation is completed.</para>
		</summary>
		<param name="ar">The result of the asynchronous operation.</param>
		<remarks>
			<para><see cref="System.AsyncCallback"/>
provides a way for client applications to complete an asynchronous
operation. This callback delegate is supplied to the client when
the asynchronous operation is initiated. The event handler referenced
by <see cref="System.AsyncCallback"/> contains program logic to finish processing the asynchronous task
for the client.</para>
			<para><see cref="System.AsyncCallback"/> uses the <see cref="System.IAsyncResult"/> interface to obtain the
status of the asynchronous operation.</para>
		</remarks>
		<seealso cref="System.IAsyncResult"/>
		<seealso topic="cpconEventsDelegates"/>
	</doc></docs>
